column5:
Adjust serialization tests

I believe this is due to the support for unserializing with changed
visibility, which will assign to the private x/y properties now.
Adjust for PHP 8 negative array key change
Avoid static call to non-static method
Case-insensitive constants are no longer supported
(unset) casts are no longer supported since PHP 8

Fix constant uses in basic.phpt

These are no longer legal in PHP 8. This is supposed to be testing
dynamic function calls, for which we should be using the string and
not rely on the bareword fallback.
Update spec for by-ref list RFC

Revert "Define encoding of PHP scripts"

This reverts commit f35bd70531c012544e9061731415be8dcfe77f32.

Define encoding of PHP scripts

1. Remove references to unicode codepoints (as those were ambigouous
without a defined encoding) and replace them with byte values
2. Define the encoding of PHP scripts as ASCII, where bytes greater than
0x7F are allowed

Mark instanceof as left-associative

May not have been originally intended this way, but it's how the
language works right now, so specify it as such (#226).

Fix precedence of by-ref assignment

Because it has variables on both sides, this is a primary expression.

Use PHP 7.3 on Travis

Apparently the master/nightly builds haven't updated since
September...

Adjust constant warning message for PHP 7.3

The spec already correctly mentions that resources are allowed.
The warning was clarified in PHP 7.3.

Add trialing comma description for constructs and functions

* Add trailing comma for
  - isset and unset
  - static and dynamic methods
  - functions and closure as functions
  - new statement
* Add or change the related tests to support the trialing comma

Sync final newlines

- Redundant final newlines trimmed into one
- Missing final newlines added where can be added

According to POSIX, a line is a sequence of zero or more non-' <newline>'
characters plus a terminating '<newline>' character. [1] Files should
normally have at least one final newline character although not
mandatory.

[1] http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/basedefs/V1_chap03.html#tag_03_206

Fix typo in spec/

And remove trailing whitespace

Fixes #217: Incorrect rule for `trait-select-insteadof-clause`

An example of the insteadof clause (satisfies the fixed rule):

`use T1,T2,T3{T1::foo insteadof T2,T3;}`

Fix typos in the unit tests (comments/messages)

Detected by https://github.com/client9/misspell

Fix typos in the specification markdown

Detected by https://github.com/client9/misspell

Fix description on how to run the tests

As of commit 8af91fd41cf74b67324b04455d904f095c6a3280 all tests are
PHPTs, and make_phpt has been removed.  We adjust the docs accordingly.

Fix statement capitalization

just making it consistent with the other items in the list.
Note that LHS of :: can also be an object
Point to GH issues in README
Mention generated files + pre-commit hook in CONTRIBUTING

Fix grammar for breakout-level

The optional breakout-level constant for `break` and `continue`
statements can also be enclosed in parentheses.

Fix some references

These got left behind after shuffling things around too much.
Move echo and unset from intrinsics to statements

Move list() out of intrinsic section

This is not a general-purpose expression, it is only valid in
specific syntactic contexts.
yield has higher precedence than AND

Move pre-inc/dec and shell-exec into primary expression

Otherwise the precedence would be wrong...

Merge postfix-expression into postfix-expression

The distinction is not meaningful, these are also primary
expressions.

Fix precedence of instanceof/logical not

Fixes #189.

Don't require statement after label

Fixes #190.
Fix definition list rendering on GitHub in Terms and Definitions
Use variable in RHS of byref-assignment

Fix precedence of coalesce operator

Fix #201.

Add missing comma in const-elements production

Fixes #205.
Account for deprecation notice in (unset) test

Reflect changes for RFC: Deprecate and Remove Bareword (Unquoted) Strings

https://wiki.php.net/rfc/deprecate-bareword-strings
fix anonymous-function-creation-expression definition - reverse ordering of return-type and anonymous-function-use-clause
add travis CI badge in README
Update tests to be compatible with master
Fix typo in anon func grammar

Fix grammar markup

Instead of <a name=""> use id attribute on <i> tag of the
definition.

Extract grammar

Grammar is now defined in <!-- GRAMMAR --> blocks. The actually
displayed grammar will be auto-generated.

Cleanup echo/isset/unset grammar

isset and unset accept only variables.
For echo, merge the single and multiple expression cases.

Improve check_refs

Handle manual anchor. Return exit code.
Restrict LHS of assignments to variable

Remove array-intrinsic

This is already covered by array-creation-operator.

Simplify `print` rule.

`print 42` is the same than `print(42)`, which is the same than
`print (42)`. Just like `echo`, it is possible to consider that
parenthesis belong to the expression instead of to the `print`
intrinsic.

Remove php-spec-draft file

GitHub doesn't redirect symlinks, so this isn't really useful to
keep around.
Fix formatting errors in grammar blocks

Remove sub-headings from grammar

These don't provide a lot of value for an overview grammar listing,
but make automatic regeneration of the grammar hard (because they
do not correspond to the headings in the actual spec -- some headings
are left out, others aren't and none of this follows any obvious
rule).

Add redundant include/require productions

The parenthesized forms are part of expression.
Make description of variable syntax more correct

`exit` with no parenthesis does have an opt. expr.

`exit` is valid, `exit(42)` is valid, but `exit 42` is invalid. The
optional expression must be surrounded by parenthesis.

Make switch-statement definition more precise

`case-statement` and `default-statement` usages must occur inside a `switch-statement`. Update the spec to represent this behavior more precisely in the grammar, rather than as an additional constraint.

fix orphaned try-statement in `19-grammar.md`

`statement` should point to `try-statement`. This now matches the
definition in `11-statements.md`
Add missing backticks that break the markup.

Move literal production to syntactic grammar

Not all literals are supported everywhere. Move to syntactic
grammar to allow the distinction.

Fix the whitespace definition.

The vertical tab and the form-feed character are not part of the
whitespaces.
b-prefix is case-insensitive and applies to doc strings
Move undefined var description to locals
Specify that qualified constant uses throw Error
Specify handling of undefined variables, constants, etc.
Punctuators: Fix spacing, add namespace separator

Remove =& from list of operators

=& is actually = followed by &.
Can also defined multiple properties at once
Multiple constants can be defined at once

Test fixes

* New __METHOD__ value for closures
* Missing pass-by-ref notice for object

Add the accepted RFC: class constant visibility to spec

RFC: https://wiki.php.net/rfc/class_const_visibility

Add support of negative string offsets

Additional fix: string are extended padding with spaces, not '\0'.
bugfix #71572: Assignment from empty string does not insert null byte anymore.

Sync grammar file

Was hoping to automate this, but the heading structure is too
different :/

Use ``` instead of <pre> for VSlot graphics

So <pre> is only used for the grammar and easy to seach for.
Fix a typo in the float-literal rule

Warn about invalid strings in arithmetic

- add variadic unpacking

Must be all on one line...

 * Clarify that a sign is supported (which is not the case for

 * Clarify that we only support decimal digits or float literals

Fixed wrong whitespaces

Microsoft Word randomly included weird whitespaces. The hexcode
for the regular whitespace is '20'. These wrong whitespaces are
in fact two characters with codes 'C2 A0'. Depending on your
editor, you'll see an error or a regular whitespace.

Merge pull request #5 from javiereguiluz/fix_word_ligatures

* javiereguiluz/fix_word_ligatures:
  Replaced word ligatures by correct characters

Replaced word ligatures by correct characters

The original document was created using Microsoft Word.
Taht's why some words contained ligatures joining two
characters. Example: "deﬁnition" instead of "definition"

Replaced regular apostrophes by "typewriter apostrophes"

This is again a problem caused by writing the original document
using Microsoft Word. The ortographic apostrophes (‘ and ’) aren't
used in technical documents, because you cannot easily write them
with the IDEs and text editors used by developers.

The solution is to use the "typewriter apostrophe" (') in both cases.
